Chennai-born Harris Jayaraj had music foisted on him from an early age. His father—a guitarist and film composer—made him learn classical guitar and begin Carnatic music training when he was just six. After scoring the highest marks in Asia for his 4th grade exam, he began his career at age 12. Having worked under the likes of Raj-Koti, A.R. Rahman and Mani Sharma, he made his debut with Minnale, for which he won the Filmfare Award for Best Music Director. This also ended A.R. Rahman's nine-year-long winning streak. Enjoy his greatest work with this playlist.
